# Directory Structure Validation Rule

## Rule
All PHP classes must be placed under the `app/` directory within each module.

## Pattern
- ❌ `Modules/{Module}/{ClassName}.php`
- ❌ `Modules/{Module}/Actions/{ClassName}.php`
- ✅ `Modules/{Module}/app/Actions/{ClassName}.php`

## Automatic Fix
```bash
# For a single file
mkdir -p Modules/{Module}/app/$(dirname {FilePath})
mv Modules/{Module}/{FilePath} Modules/{Module}/app/{FilePath}

# For a directory (e.g., Actions)
mkdir -p Modules/{Module}/app/Actions
mv Modules/{Module}/Actions/* Modules/{Module}/app/Actions/
rmdir Modules/{Module}/Actions
```

## Common Directories to Check
- Actions/
- Console/
- Exceptions/
- Filament/
- Http/
- Models/
- Policies/
- Providers/
- Resources/
